{
  "texts": [
    "MCI is a condition where a person experiences mild cognitive decline beyond that of what would normally be expected for their age.",
    "Dementia is a more severe form of cognitive decline that affects multiple cognitive domains and interferes with a person's ability to carry out daily activities [70].Computer-Aided Diagnosis (CAD) techniques have been developed to help detect and diagnose cognitive impairments.",
    "These techniques involve the use of computer algorithms to analyze various types of data such as brain scans, medical records, and cognitive tests.",
    "For example, MRI can be used to identify structural changes in the brain that are indicative of cognitive impairment [22].",
    "Deep learning algorithms can be trained on these images to help identify patterns and predict the likelihood of cognitive impairment [21,31]."
  ]
}